        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You offer to broker a pact of peace. If the target accepts and doesn't take hostile actions against you and your allies, you take a -1 status penalty to Deception checks to Lie to them. If they refuse and take a hostile action against you or an ally, they must attempt a Will save. If they accepted the offer and then take a hostile action against you or an ally, they must attempt a Will save and treat the result as one category worse. Regardless of the outcome, the target is then temporarily immune for 1 minute.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target takes a -1 status penalty to attack and damage rolls against you and your allies.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The target takes a -2 status penalty to attack and damage rolls against you and your allies.</p>"
